Description: Corroded copper alloy thick rectangular seal, for stamping on jar-sealings, with a plumed and disked vertical cartouche deeply incised, containing the nomen of Amasis preceded and followed by the epithets "Perfect God" and "Son of Neith"; a large ring-handle is welded in the middle of the backside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19
Curator's comments: The "bronze stamp of Aahmes", mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 76, p. 111, pl. xli, 76 Being studied as part of PhD by Elisabeth Greifenstein (University of Wuerzburg).
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, p. 111, pl. xli, 76.)
Hall 1913 / Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs, etc. in the British Museum (2742, p. 284)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.45, p.46, p.66, p.182, pl.24)
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 2011 Mar-Oct, Dumwich Museum, The Dunwich Seal
